					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-631760#post-2324831</guid>
				<title>Re: Our motto is secure, contain, protect, not Destroy!Destroy!Destroy!</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-631760/scp-1476#post-2324831</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2015 15:37:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>church1alpha</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2146859</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Well, considering that they can theoretically replicate endlessly, they could potentially wipe out all other species of goose. In the context of &quot;biohazard&quot; (hope that's the right category) and &quot;possibly uncontained,&quot; I agree with the Euclid classification. Just my personal opinion, though.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
